✅ Selenium Python Installation Guide

1. Install Python 
    -> Go to official website https://www.python.org/
    -> Download the latest and stable version
    -> IMPORTANT , while installing "ADD Python to PATH" 
    -> Click install now

    Verify Installation now
    ------------------------
    python --version or py --version

2. Installation Selenium using pip

    -> pip install selenium or py -m pip install selenium (m-> multiple python Installations)
        
        Verify selenium Installation
        ----------------------------
        pip show selenium -> should show the selenium package version

3. Install a browser 
    -> Chrome
    -> FireFox
    -> Edge
4. WebDriver Setup
    Using selenium Manager
    ----------------------
    If you installed latest Selenium, it automatically downloads driver.

    Example:
    from selenium import WebDriver
    driver=WebDriver.FireFox()
    driver.get("https://www.google.com")

    👉 No manual driver downloaded

5. Run a sample script
    -> Create a file: test.py

    test.py
    -------
    from selenium import webdriver

    driver = webdriver.Chrome()
    driver.get("https://www.google.com")
    print(driver.title)
    driver.quit()

    Run:
    ---
    python test.py
    
If browser opens → ✅ Installation successful

